    "description": "Manappuram Finance Global Group invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Senior Financial Analyst at our Coimbatore location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Manappuram Finance Global Group:\nManappuram Finance Global Group is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manappuram Finance Global Group!",
